===對這場比賽的平民抗議活動===
該國的{{le|巴林人權中心|Bahrain Centre for Human Rights|人權團體}}在2012年1月力勸各隊在該國持續進行衝突中，聯合抵制這場比賽。<ref>{{cite news|title=F1 teams urged to boycott Bahrain Grand Prix|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/f1-teams-urged-boycott-bahrain-grand-prix-438970.html|first=Claire|last=Ferris-lay|work=Arabian Business|publisher=ITP Publishing Group|date=2012-01-08|accessdate=2012-03-25|archive-date=2012-02-25|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/65iqlhUkF?url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/f1-teams-urged-boycott-bahrain-grand-prix-438970.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>一個自稱{{le|2月14日青年同盟|February 14 Youth Coalition}}的抗議組織在2月寫信給伯尼·埃克萊斯頓，威脅若是比賽進行的話，他們將「在他們的能力範圍內讓比賽以失敗收場」。<ref>{{cite news|title=F1 boss Bernie Ecclestone trusts Bahrain Grand Prix will be safe|url=http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98096|first=Jonathan|last=Noble|work=Autosport|publisher=Haymarket Publications|date=2012-03-17|accessdate=2012-03-25|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303220024/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98096|dead-url=no}}</ref>他們更補充說明如果比賽照常，他們將無法保證車隊、車手和觀眾的安全。<ref>{{cite news|title=Bahrain youth group targets Formula 1 (registration required)|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/28d014a6-8179-11e1-8aae-00144feab49a,Authorised=false.html?_i_location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcms%2Fs%2F0%2F28d014a6-8179-11e1-8aae-00144feab49a.html&_i_referer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.f1fanatic.co.uk%2F2012%2F04%2F09%2Ff1-fanatic-roundup-94%2F#axzz1rUodhoQq|first=Simeon|last=Kerr|work=[[Financial_Times|Financial Times]]|publisher=[[Pearson_PLC|Pearson PLC]]|date=2012-04-08|accessdate=2012-04-09|archive-date=2016-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306031521/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/28d014a6-8179-11e1-8aae-00144feab49a,Authorised=false.html?_i_location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcms%2Fs%2F0%2F28d014a6-8179-11e1-8aae-00144feab49a.html&_i_referer=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.f1fanatic.co.uk%2F2012%2F04%2F09%2Ff1-fanatic-roundup-94%2F#axzz1rUodhoQq|dead-url=no}}</ref>埃克萊斯頓並不擔心這次的恐嚇，說道他不覺得示威者需要訴諸暴力，並相信賽事主辦方不會對任何武力反抗作出回應。而[[F1世界車手冠軍列表|世界車手冠軍]][[賽巴斯蒂安·維特爾|賽巴斯蒂安·維特爾]]及[[麥可·舒馬克|麥可·舒馬克]]同樣也贊同照常舉行這場比賽。<ref name="GNews">{{cite news|title=Bahrain youths protest against Formula One|url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5hrs4t94gX6vt9ZYYgQ7Sk-iclPeA?docId=CNG.128e7c3df939aae66479f5f1f04d4b9c.5a1|work=[[Google_News|Google News]]|publisher=[[Google|Google]]|agency=[[Agence_France-Presse|Agence France-Presse]]|date=2012-04-01|accessdate=2012-04-02|archive-date=2012-04-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120407061729/http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5hrs4t94gX6vt9ZYYgQ7Sk-iclPeA?docId=CNG.128e7c3df939aae66479f5f1f04d4b9c.5a1|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2012年3月28日，埃克萊斯頓證實這場賽事將照常舉辦。<ref>{{cite news|title=On Bahrain|url=http://willthef1journo.wordpress.com/2012/03/29/on-bahrain/|first=Will|last=Buxton|work=The Buxton Blog|publisher=Will Buxton|date=2012-03-29|accessdate=2012-03-30|archive-date=2020-09-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200921040249/https://willthef1journo.wordpress.com/2012/03/29/on-bahrain/|dead-url=no}}</ref>四天後，示威者重啟他們對這場比賽的抗議，而警方則終止了{{le|阿布赛巴|Abu Saiba}}和{{le|都柏利|Tubli}}的示威活動。積極分子也轉向了[[Twitter|Twitter]]，以努力讓這場比賽被取消。<ref name="GNews"/>據報導，在四月的第一週結束前，抗議活動的重點已經轉移到了這場比賽上，而積極分子指控政府利用這場比賽來「欺騙國際社會，告知他們一切都已恢復正常」。<ref>{{cite news|title=Bahrain Activist’s Hunger Strike Belies Image of Calm Ahead of Formula One Race|url=http://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/04/06/bahrain-activists-hunger-strike-belies-image-of-calm-ahead-of-formula-one-race/|first=Robert|last=Mackey|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|publisher=Arthur Ochs Sulzberger, Jr.; The New York Times Company|date=2012-04-07|accessdate=2012-04-08|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111224737/https://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/04/06/bahrain-activists-hunger-strike-belies-image-of-calm-ahead-of-formula-one-race/|dead-url=no}}</ref>然而，政府回絕了這些說法，而賽道主席扎耶德·阿勒扎亞尼（Zayed al-Zayani）是以所有涉及的利益為出發點來提出這場比賽，且會為這個區域帶來不容小覷的經濟利益。阿勒扎亞尼進一步宣稱，他並不明白為何這場比賽會被轉變為一個政治議題，反而說道「比賽持續在準備中，因為巴林是中東賽車運動的主場」，<ref>{{cite news|title=Sakhir circuit chief says Bahrain Grand Prix would help nation recover|url=http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98651|first=Jonathan|last=Noble|work=Autosport|publisher=Haymarket Publications|date=2012-04-07|accessdate=2012-04-08|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304054138/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98651|dead-url=no}}</ref>並指責了想利用這場比賽製造道德恐慌的「空談的旁觀者」和「危言聳聽的極端分子」。<ref name="lotus f1 report">{{cite news|title=Bahrain chairman Zayed Al Zayani says 'scaremongering extremists' are the cause for alarm over the Sakhir event|url=http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98693|first=Matt|last=Beer|work=Autosport|publisher=Haymarket Publications|date=2012-04-10|accessdate=2012-04-10|archive-date=2016-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112012024/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98693|dead-url=no}}</ref>另一方面，{{le|巴林人權中心|Bahrain Centre for Human Rights|激進主義分子}}則否認了這些說法，並重申他們認為政府仍試圖利用這場比賽「告訴外界整起事件已經恢復平和」且「他們想要脫離孤立，才會說這一切都已恢復正常了」。<ref name="indifference"/>

在反比賽抗議後，埃克萊斯頓承認如果車隊不想在巴林出賽的話，他也沒有權力強制他們。<ref>{{cite news|title=Ecclestone steps back over Bahrain (subscription required)|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/tto/news/world/article/3379239.ece/|work=The Times|publisher=[[News_Corporation|News Corporation]]|date=2012-040-9|accessdate=2012-04-10}}</ref>同日，《[[衛報|衛報]]》引述了一位不具名的車隊主席的話，指出他「身體不適」無法前往巴林，又說「他們（主辦方）能安然無事地辦完這場比賽的唯一辦法，就是有一支完整的軍隊在那管制進出。而我認為這無論是對F1或是對巴林來說都是無法令人滿意的。但是我想不到其他辦法了。」<ref name="team principal">{{cite news|title=F1 teams want FIA to postpone Bahrain Grand Prix|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/apr/09/formula-one-bahrain-grand-prix|first=Paul|last=Weaver|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|publisher=Guardian News and Media|date=2012-04-09|accessdate=2012-04-10|archive-date=2013-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130502205800/http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/apr/09/formula-one-bahrain-grand-prix|dead-url=no}}</ref>他也承認儘管在比賽兩週前，[[外交及國協事務部|外交及國協事務部]]並沒有對巴林發出任何旅遊限制，<ref>{{cite news|title=Spotlight intensifies on Bahrain GP|url=http://www.jamesallenonf1.com/2012/04/spotlight-intensifies-on-bahrain-gp/|first=James|last=Allen|work=James Allen on F1|publisher=James Allen|date=2012-04-09|accessdate=2012-04-10|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304001726/http://www.jamesallenonf1.com/2012/04/spotlight-intensifies-on-bahrain-gp/|dead-url=no}}</ref>且車隊的保險公司也對前往該國沒有異議，<ref name="F1F 10-4">{{cite news|title=F1's Bahrain Grand Prix brinkmanship is all about money|url=http://www.f1fanatic.co.uk/2012/04/10/f1-brinkmanship-bahrain-grand-prix-money/|first=Keith|last=Collantine|work=F1 Fanatic|publisher=Keith Collantine|date=2012-04-10|accessdate=2012-04-10|archive-date=2017-09-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170903042452/http://www.f1fanatic.co.uk/2012/04/10/f1-brinkmanship-bahrain-grand-prix-money/|dead-url=no}}</ref>但仍有幾支車隊仍對於比賽的進行持保留態度。<ref name="F1F 10-4"/>因為這場比賽被安排在{{F1 GP|2012|中國}}的一週後，以防巴林大獎賽被取消，據稱車隊已經收到了兩份來回機票（一份從上海直達英格蘭；另一份從上海到英格蘭，中途停靠巴林）。<ref name="team principal"/>埃克萊斯頓則輕輕帶過這些評論，稱十二支車隊中沒有任何一支車隊對於出賽向他表示異議，並補充說任何沒有出賽的車隊將違反[[協和協議|協和協議]]，且有可能將面臨罰款。<ref>{{cite news|title=Bernie Ecclestone tells F1 teams to pay up or shut up over Bahrain|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/apr/10/f1-bernie-ecclestone-bahrain-grand-prix|first=Paul|last=Weaver|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|publisher=Guardian News and Media|date=2012-04-10|accessdate=2012-04-10|archive-date=2012-04-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120423121142/http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport/2012/apr/10/f1-bernie-ecclestone-bahrain-grand-prix|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===國際汽聯的回應===
在巴林賽事前一週的中國大獎賽籌備期間，扎耶德·阿勒扎亞尼注意到了一份受[[路特斯車隊|路特斯車隊]]委託的報告，預測這場比賽的抗議活動將僅限於和平示威，除了警力略顯增加之外，觀眾並不會注意到這場比賽與[[2010年巴林大獎賽|2010年]]和2012年賽事之間的差異。<ref name="lotus f1 report"/>這份路特斯的報告經過了[[倫敦警察廳|倫敦警察廳]]前{{le|倫敦警察廳助理總監|Assistant Commissioner of Police of the Metropolis|助理總監}}及[[巴林內政部|巴林內政部]]顧問{{le|約翰·耶茨 (警官)|John Yates (police officer)|約翰·耶茨}}簡報的證實，並聲明抗議活動是非法的且被報導歪曲。<ref name="Yates">{{cite news|title=FIA reassured Bahrain Grand Prix will be safe|url=http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98707|first=Jonathan|last=Noble|work=Autosport|publisher=Haymarket Publications|date=2012-04-12|accessdate=2012-04-12|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303215555/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98707|dead-url=no}}</ref>耶茨隨後承認巴林政府沒有辦法在比賽期間保證任何人的安全，且保安部隊在大獎賽期間的衝突事件中，將可能被迫使用真槍實彈和致命武器。<ref>{{cite news|title=Bahrain unable to guarantee safety for Formula One says former Met officer|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2012/apr/18/bahrain-formula-one-yates-safety|first=Paul|last=Weaver|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|publisher=Guardian Media Group|date=2012-04-18|accessdate=2012-04-19|archive-date=2012-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121118013753/http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2012/apr/18/bahrain-formula-one-yates-safety|dead-url=no}}</ref>在此之後又警告抗議活動可能會造成傷亡，<ref>{{cite news|title=Bahrain Grand Prix 2012: thousands march in peaceful protest as former politician admits to fears over casualties|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/motorsport/formulaone/9209377/Bahrain-Grand-Prix-2012-thousands-march-in-peaceful-protest-as-former-politician-admits-to-fears-over-casualties.html|first=Tom|last=Cary|work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]]|publisher=[[Telegraph_Media_Group|Telegraph Media Group]]|date=2012-04-17|accessdate=2012-04-19|archive-date=2018-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181002062654/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/motorsport/formulaone/9209377/Bahrain-Grand-Prix-2012-thousands-march-in-peaceful-protest-as-former-politician-admits-to-fears-over-casualties.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{le|巴林人權中心|Bahrain Centre for Human Rights}}主席{{le|納比勒·拉傑卜|Nabeel Rajab}}則保證一級方程式賽車場內不會有人因示威活動受傷，且示威對這項運動並不是一場人身攻擊，而是針對這場比賽繼續舉辦的政治影響。<ref>{{cite news|title='No-one in F1 will be hurt' – Humans Rights leader|url=http://www.gpupdate.net/en/f1-news/277451/no-one-in-f1-will-be-hurt-humans-rights-leader/|work=GPUpdate.net|publisher=GPUpdate|date=2012-04-19|accessdate=2012-04-19|archive-date=2019-09-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190911193056/https://www.autosport.com/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
{{quote box|quote=「我特別關注那些與F1有密切關聯——車手、車隊、贊助商、媒體和有意出席的支持者——而被扭曲事實的事物。這樣的局面正在透過大量從社群媒體論壇傳播的不精確且虛假的訊息形成。而一些麻煩確實仍存在著。幾乎每晚在特定村莊發生的小規模動亂是進步的潛在障礙，更讓那些維護治安及無辜的社會大眾陷於危險之中。然而，不管這些事件如何透過YouTube和其他途徑傳播，他們的含意也不應該被過分誇大。這些經過允許的屬法律上正當的示威活動，但仍有通常由15－20位年輕人組成的小群體暴力行為。這些對正在執行鎮壓、手無寸鐵的警察部隊進行攻擊是犯法的。這些人正在蓄意傷害警方以及他們所生活的社會。但他們並不能代表我每日看到討人喜歡、奉公守法的絕大多數巴林市民。現在我與我的家人在一起，我感到非常的安全。的確，這裡比我有時在倫敦感到的來的安全。」|source=2012年4月12日，[[倫敦警察廳|倫敦警察廳]]前助理總監{{le|約翰·耶茨 (警官)|John Yates (police officer)|約翰·耶茨}}向國際汽聯與一級方程式賽車車隊簡報。<ref name="Yates"/>}}
[[一級方程式車隊協會|一級方程式車隊協會]]的成員對比賽將被取消的媒體猜測做出回應，表示他們並沒有取消一場大獎賽的權力，<ref>{{cite news|title=Formula One Teams' Association says that decision over Bahrain GP is down to FIA|url=http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98696|first=Jonathan|last=Noble|work=Autosport|publisher=Haymarket Publications|date=2012-04-11|accessdate=2012-04-11|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303222125/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98696|dead-url=no}}</ref>而伯尼·埃克萊斯頓也宣布這場比賽只會在巴林當局的要求下取消。<ref>{{cite news|title=Ecclestone says Bahrain race is on|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/2012/04/12/uk-motor-racing-bahrain-ecclestone-idUKBRE83B0BX20120412|first=Alan|last=Baldwin|work=[[Reuters|Reuters]]|publisher=[[Thomson_Reuters|Thomson Reuters]]|date=2012-04-12|accessdate=2012-04-12|archive-date=2015-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150614071642/http://uk.reuters.com/article/2012/04/12/uk-motor-racing-bahrain-ecclestone-idUKBRE83B0BX20120412|dead-url=no}}</ref>當被問到他們對巴林大獎賽的看法時，[[麥拉倫車隊|麥拉倫]]和[[紅牛車隊|紅牛]]的車手[[簡森·巴頓|簡森·巴頓]]及[[馬克·韋伯|馬克·韋伯]]皆呼籲這項運動在此議題上要團結，並請國際汽聯盡可能地做出明確的決定。<ref>{{cite news|title=Jenson Button says F1 must remain united over Bahrain Grand Prix|url=http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98732|first=Jonathan|last=Noble|work=Autosport|publisher=Haymarket Publications|date=2012-04-12|accessdate=2012-04-12|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304002840/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98732|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Webber says F1 drivers have no choice but to trust FIA to make right call on Bahrain|url=http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98729|first1=Jonathan|last1=Noble|first2=Edd|last2=Straw|work=Autosport|publisher=Haymarket Publications|date=2012-04-12|accessdate=2012-04-12|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303223255/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/98729|dead-url=no}}</ref>

